[SN]TITLE[SN]
Election 2015: UKIP seeks more money for Wales

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
UKIP is promising to secure more funding for Wales, as it launches its Welsh manifesto for the general election.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
It says it will change the Treasury's Barnett formula in favour of Welsh and English taxpayers "disadvantaged" in favour of Scotland "for so long".
UKIP also proposes making St David's Day a public holiday.
The party will also call for the abolition of the Severn Bridge tolls by 2018 at an event in Merthyr Tydfil.
UKIP is standing in all 40 seats in Wales as it seeks to get its first Welsh MP elected.
The Welsh Conservatives will also launch their manifesto on Friday.
